                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15205758" author="ram_krish" created="Tue, 22 Mar 2016 04:17:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Better to convert all these as subtasks. &lt;br/&gt;
So familyMap has to do a clone() every time. That is generating lot of garbage. But I don&apos;t think we can avoid that copy if a Map with byte[] is used. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15205788" author="stack" created="Tue, 22 Mar 2016 04:47:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A start might be purging references to family Map from public API then we could start doing something else (CellBlocks!!!)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15205870" author="anoop.hbase" created="Tue, 22 Mar 2016 06:16:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;At least in server side we can avoid and having things like CellBlock or cell array?  Because there the cells are coming in order. &lt;br/&gt;
In a recent PE test I noticed this. The BufferedMutator having a 2 MB flush size. But the actual data coming to RS is not even 1 MB in size !!&lt;br/&gt;
So in server side also we add up all these extra Java object overhead !!!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15205873" author="anoop.hbase" created="Tue, 22 Mar 2016 06:17:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One thing need to consider may that, the pre hooks like prePut passes the Mutation and allows user to add/remove cells.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
